{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EGW572i8FoCg9FQhvbnDxX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→spring.application.name=Address Book (Spring + JSF)\n     2→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:addressbook;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n     3→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     4→spring.datasource.password=\n     5→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update\n     6→spring.jpa.show-sql=true\n     7→spring.mvc.format.date=MM/dd/yyyy\n     8→spring.messages.basename=Bundle,ValidationMessages\n     9→server.port=8080\n    10→\n    11→# JSF Configuration\n    12→joinfaces.faces-servlet.enabled=true\n    13→joinfaces.faces-servlet.url-mappings=*.xhtml,/faces/*\n    14→joinfaces.jsf.project-stage=Development\n    15→\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HbFy8SPLTveBghsCrPfJEX","session_id":"d9614706-aa1e-4ee0-a2cc-4f8232e667d9","uuid":"c4e67c2c-89d7-4d50-9b25-e7c53308aa04"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HbFy8SPLTveBghsCrPfJEX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me summarize my findings for you:\n\n1. Complete File Tree:\nMain project structure:\n- /output\n  ├── .dockerignore\n  ├── .mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.properties\n  ├── Dockerfile\n  ├── mvnw\n  ├── mvnw.cmd\n  ├── pom.xml\n  └── src/\n      └── main/\n          ├── java/com/example/addressbookspring/\n          │   ├── Application.java\n          │   ├── ServletInitializer.java\n          │   ├── config/\n          │   │   ├── JsfConfig.java\n          │   │   └── SpringConfig.java\n          │   ├── entity/\n          │   │   └── Contact.java\n          │   ├── repo/\n          │   │   └── ContactRepository.java\n          │   ├── service/\n          │   │   └── ContactService.java\n          │   └── web/\n          │       └── ContactController.java\n          └── resources/\n              ├── Bundle.properties\n              ├── application.properties\n              ├── ValidationMessages.properties\n              └── META-INF/\n                  ├── faces-config.xml\n                  └── resources/\n                      ├── contact/\n                      │   ├── Create.xhtml\n                      │   ├── Edit.xhtml\n                      │   ├── List.xhtml\n                      │   └── View.xhtml\n                      ├── css/\n                      │   └── jsfcrud.css\n                      └── index.xhtml\n\n2. Build System: Maven (pom.xml)\n   - Spring Boot version: Implicitly 3.x (from dependencies)\n   - Java version: 17\n   - Packaging: WAR\n   - Key dependencies:\n     * spring-boot-starter-data-jpa\n     * spring-boot-starter-web\n     * spring-boot-starter-validation\n     * joinfaces-jsf-spring-boot-starter\n     * h2 database (runtime)\n\n3. Spring Version: \n   - Core Spring version: 6.2.11\n   - Spring Boot: 3.x (implied)\n\n4. Jakarta Imports Found:\n   - Jakarta Persistence: @Entity, @Id, @GeneratedValue, @Temporal\n   - Jakarta Validation: @NotNull, @Past, @Pattern\n   - Jakarta Faces: FacesContext, FacesServlet, FacesMessage\n   - All javax.* imports have been migrated to jakarta.*\n\n5. Dockerfile Details:\n   - Uses maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble base image\n   - Sets up Python venv and Playwright\n   - Copies project files\n   - Runs mvn clean package spring-boot:run\n\n6. Configuration:\n   - Uses H2 in-memory database\n   - Hibernate DDL auto: update\n   - JSF configured via JoinFaces starter\n   - Development project stage\n\n7. Architecture:\n   - Layered architecture: \n     * Entity: Contact\n     * Repository: ContactRepository (JpaRepository)\n     * Service: ContactService\n     * Web: ContactController (using JSF)\n\n8. Test Files: None found in this exploration\n\nSignificant Migration Notes:\n- Successfully migrated from javax.* to jakarta.* namespace\n- Uses Jakarta EE 10 compatible libraries\n- Spring Boot 3.x compatible project\n- JSF integrated via JoinFaces starter\n\nWould you like me to dive deeper into any specific aspect of this project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9614706-aa1e-4ee0-a2cc-4f8232e667d9","uuid":"9d5cb093-839e-4136-a88f-ca67e1b374b7"}
